casebody.data:
State of Connecticut v. James McClinden (9658)

Dupont, C. J., Daly and O’Connell, Js.

Argued October 4 decision released October 29, 1991 Donald D. Dakers, public defender, for the appellant (defendant). LeonF. Dalbec, Jr., assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Michael Dearington, state’s attorney, and Robert J. O’Brien, supervisory assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
